{"id":14881483,"mediaExerciseId":"e3bc623b-b703-4d71-b1cd-087bd9f5f91a","exerciseName":"31","chapterName":"14","chapterTitle":"Cost of Capital","groupId":612388,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":493,"solutions":[{"id":6404227,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we will analyze the value of a company based on the relative movement of its assets and earnings. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"A company's value is solved from the earnings, depreciation, net working capital as well as capital spending. \n\nAs indicated in the problem, there is no change in these values throughout the whole period. If there is also no change in the tax rate for the company, then we can say for certain that **the value of the company remains the same** since these values that are considered in the valuation of a company did not change. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"781508a4-b568-4b04-948f-9723f779fed5","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":2}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id"